<paragraph id="9C06487CFFE8964EFF5BF3B16630FE66" blockId="4.[151,1436,1940,2039]" lastBlockId="7.[151,1437,151,501]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="365" pageId="4" pageNumber="362">
<emphasis id="AECD946EFFE8964DFF5BF3B16395F841" bold="true" box="[199,461,1976,2002]" pageId="4" pageNumber="362">External morphology.</emphasis>
Body (
<figureCitation id="048254F9FFE8964DFDBCF3B160C3F841" box="[544,667,1976,2002]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1887,1911]" captionTargetBox="[165,1426,193,1851]" captionTargetId="figure-17@6.[151,1436,181,1863]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Hatigoria longistylia Tang &amp; Zhang n. sp., Holotype ♂: A. Habitus, dorsal view; B. Habitus, lateral view; C. Head, dorsal view; D. Face; E. Pygofer, lateral view; F. Pygofer, dorsal view; G. Pygofer, ventral view; H. Connective and style, ventral view; I. Aedeagus, dorsal view; J. Subgenital plate, ventral view; K. Aedeagus, lateral view. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141617" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141617/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="362">Fig. 3A–D</figureCitation>
) usually yellow brown. Crown (
<figureCitation id="048254F9FFE8964DFB9BF3B16605F841" box="[1031,1117,1976,2002]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1887,1911]" captionTargetBox="[165,1426,193,1851]" captionTargetId="figure-17@6.[151,1436,181,1863]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Hatigoria longistylia Tang &amp; Zhang n. sp., Holotype ♂: A. Habitus, dorsal view; B. Habitus, lateral view; C. Head, dorsal view; D. Face; E. Pygofer, lateral view; F. Pygofer, dorsal view; G. Pygofer, ventral view; H. Connective and style, ventral view; I. Aedeagus, dorsal view; J. Subgenital plate, ventral view; K. Aedeagus, lateral view. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141617" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141617/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="362">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
) more than 3.0x longer than wide; anterior process slightly curved dorsad with margins parallel in lateral view, with lateral ridge simple and legible, unbranched; ocelli not very outstanding, median longitudinal carina strong but absent near base, apical half slightly recurved upward and sword-shaped in lateral view. Face (
<figureCitation id="048254F9FFEB964EFCE5F4B26189FF46" box="[889,977,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1887,1911]" captionTargetBox="[165,1426,193,1851]" captionTargetId="figure-17@6.[151,1436,181,1863]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Hatigoria longistylia Tang &amp; Zhang n. sp., Holotype ♂: A. Habitus, dorsal view; B. Habitus, lateral view; C. Head, dorsal view; D. Face; E. Pygofer, lateral view; F. Pygofer, dorsal view; G. Pygofer, ventral view; H. Connective and style, ventral view; I. Aedeagus, dorsal view; J. Subgenital plate, ventral view; K. Aedeagus, lateral view. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141617" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141617/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="365">Fig. 3D</figureCitation>
) with clypeal sulcus slightly arcuate, anteclypeus base with one transverse carina, one indistinct median longitudinal carina below transverse carina, apex hardly surpassing lower margin of gena and feebly truncate, antennal ridges moderately developed and declinate. Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="048254F9FFEB964EFE84F52E632AFED2" box="[280,370,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1887,1911]" captionTargetBox="[165,1426,193,1851]" captionTargetId="figure-17@6.[151,1436,181,1863]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Hatigoria longistylia Tang &amp; Zhang n. sp., Holotype ♂: A. Habitus, dorsal view; B. Habitus, lateral view; C. Head, dorsal view; D. Face; E. Pygofer, lateral view; F. Pygofer, dorsal view; G. Pygofer, ventral view; H. Connective and style, ventral view; I. Aedeagus, dorsal view; J. Subgenital plate, ventral view; K. Aedeagus, lateral view. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141617" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141617/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="365">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
) with dorsal surface mainly covered with black setae and lateral surface covered with lightcolored setae, anterior margin somewhat arcuate, depressed anterolaterally, lateral margins not ridged and a little concave, obviously longer than anterior margin. Exposed part of mesonotum (
<figureCitation id="048254F9FFEB964EFB99F5666605FE1A" box="[1029,1117,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1887,1911]" captionTargetBox="[165,1426,193,1851]" captionTargetId="figure-17@6.[151,1436,181,1863]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Hatigoria longistylia Tang &amp; Zhang n. sp., Holotype ♂: A. Habitus, dorsal view; B. Habitus, lateral view; C. Head, dorsal view; D. Face; E. Pygofer, lateral view; F. Pygofer, dorsal view; G. Pygofer, ventral view; H. Connective and style, ventral view; I. Aedeagus, dorsal view; J. Subgenital plate, ventral view; K. Aedeagus, lateral view. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141617" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141617/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="365">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
) about as long as scutellum, scutellum slightly swollen distad of scutoscutellar sulcus. Abdomen with irregular yellow patches on 4th to 6th or even 7th tergites laterally. Hind femur macrosetal formula 2+1+0, with ca. 10, 11–12 and 14–18 setae in rows AD, PD, AV respectively; tarsomere I without row of plantar setae, pecten with 11 platellae.
</paragraph>
