<subSubSection id="D4A31BF7FFE49641FF5BF62A618FFC86" pageId="8" pageNumber="366" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="9C06487CFFE49641FF5BF62A603CFDF2" blockId="8.[151,1437,150,789]" pageId="8" pageNumber="366">
<emphasis id="AECD946EFFE49641FF5BF62A6316FDAE" bold="true" box="[199,334,547,573]" pageId="8" pageNumber="366">Etymology.</emphasis>
This new species epithet is from Latin, “ 
<taxonomicName id="5BB933FFFFE49641FC88F62A61D2FDAE" authorityName="Tang &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2021" box="[788,906,547,573]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hatigoria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="366" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longistylia">
<emphasis id="AECD946EFFE49641FC88F62A61D2FDAE" box="[788,906,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="366">longistylia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” referring to its elongate head process and long branch of the ventral pygofer appendage.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9C06487CFFE49641FF5BF662618FFC86" blockId="8.[151,1437,150,789]" pageId="8" pageNumber="366">
<emphasis id="AECD946EFFE49641FF5BF6626349FD16" bold="true" box="[199,273,619,645]" pageId="8" pageNumber="366">Notes.</emphasis>
This species resembles 
<taxonomicName id="5BB933FFFFE49641FD83F66260ACFD17" authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1908" box="[543,756,619,644]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hatigoria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="366" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="praeiens">
<emphasis id="AECD946EFFE49641FD83F66260ACFD17" box="[543,756,619,644]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="366">Hatigoria praeiens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in external morphology but may be distinguished by the following characteristics: 1) head process longer and only slightly curved upward (process of 
<taxonomicName id="5BB933FFFFE49641FB09F686674FFD3B" authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1908" box="[1173,1303,655,680]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hatigoria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="366" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="praeiens">
<emphasis id="AECD946EFFE49641FB09F686674FFD3B" box="[1173,1303,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="366">H. praeiens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shorter and obviously curved upward); 2) aedeagal shaft tubular with few tiny wrinkles on dorsal surface (shaft of 
<taxonomicName id="5BB933FFFFE49641FA85F6BA67C4FD5F" authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1908" box="[1305,1436,691,716]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hatigoria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="366" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="praeiens">
<emphasis id="AECD946EFFE49641FA85F6BA67C4FD5F" box="[1305,1436,691,716]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="366">H. praeiens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with base sunken and numerous transverse wrinkles on dorsal surface); and 3) subgenital plate apex somewhat round and broad (plate apex of 
<taxonomicName id="5BB933FFFFE49641FE6BF6F26021FC87" authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1908" box="[503,633,763,788]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hatigoria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="366" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="praeiens">
<emphasis id="AECD946EFFE49641FE6BF6F26021FC87" box="[503,633,763,788]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="366">H. praeiens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
moderately acute and narrow).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
